HEADWORD: Camerate
<hw>Cam"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Camerated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Camerzting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>cameratus</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>camerare</ets>. See <er>Camber</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To build in the form of a vault; to arch over.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To divide into chambers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cameration</ent>⟦br⟧
